title: Aeneidis Libri XII
creator: Publius Vergilius Maro
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Aeneidis Libri XII, by Publius Vergilius Maro. Read by Malone. Aeneas flees the destruction of Troy, abandons Dido, queen of the Carthaginians, and wends his way to Latium in Italy, where slaying Turnus, leader of native resistance, he founds the future Rome. (Summary by Malone) For further information, including links to M4B audio book, online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
